begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves and said where we were from, she was from California.  She also mentioned that she had not done the chat before and I told her that I had done it twice.
middle_memory_text: I think it was probably about the wildfires in California and also about COVID and how it was affecting us, our families, and our communities.
end_memory_text: We talked a bit about Prolific and what kind of studies we have done and also how we spend the money we get from participating,
rest_of_day_open: It will be a busy week, my coworker is out of the office and so I will have no shortage of things to do each day.  I am looking forward to this coming Thursday, my cousin is in town for the day.  She has been really careful like me during COVID because we are both the main caretakers for our parents, so I am ok with seeing her and hugging her.
critical_positive: I think we both kept the conversation going well.  We both asked each other questions and seemed interested in getting to know one another.  We kept the conversation light and not too personal. We would find things that we had in common which was nice.  She was also younger than me and we still we had fun talking.
critical_negative: I think there was an age difference but not so much of one that it kept us from talking.  She seemed a little shy at first but she also said that she had not done the chat before so I can understand why she was maybe shy.  She looked off to the side alot but it did not bother me.

begin_memory_text: We talked about where we are from, how many pets we have, and discussed the california wildfires and texas tornadoes.
middle_memory_text: We talked about what we do for a living, then we discussed how she is studying alzheimer's disease. We talked about our families and described our nieces and nephews, how neither of us have kids.
end_memory_text: We talked about video games for a minute and how she is a very dedicated candy crush player. We also discussed why we use prolific and what kind of studies keep us interested.
rest_of_day_open: For the rest of the week, I will be doing lots of schoolwork and filing papers for work. I am excited to get my haircut on Monday, I haven't gotten my hair done in a long time so it will be a nice confidence boost. I know I have a lot of homework to do so it is going to be a very busy week.
critical_positive: My partner was very friendly and knew how to keep a conversation going. I believe since she works at a university and studies psychology she is very good around people and can make them feel comfortable. There were no awkward silences, and we were both able to share mini-stories on certain topics which were fun to tell/listen to.
critical_negative: I don't believe there was very much that went wrong in the conversation. She might have talked a little too fast for me but it still wasn't a bother at all. She talked quite a bit and the ratio might have been more towards her, but it still felt even enough of a conversation where we were both able to talk and listen.
